section.section:
A court shall remove a fiduciary who has:
Willfully misrepresented material facts leading to his appointment or to other action by the court in reference to the fiduciary estate;
Willfully disregarded an order of court;
Shown himself incapable, with or without fault to properly perform the duties of his office; or
Breached his duty of good faith or loyalty in the management of property of the fiduciary estate.
